ITSM vs HaloPSA (Detailed Gap Analysis)
======================================

Assumption
- Your ITSM includes an end-user portal for ticket submission and status tracking.

A. End-User Experience
- HaloPSA
  - Full self-service portal + service catalog.
  - Knowledge base integrated into portal.
  - Request types can be governed with approvals and automation.
- Your ITSM
  - End-user portal exists (ticket submission + status view).
  - Knowledge base removed/hidden.
  - Request types and approvals exist but are less structured than full catalog.
- Gaps
  - No service catalog.
  - No KB publishing.
  - Limited request-type automation depth.

B. Ticketing + Service Desk Core
- HaloPSA
  - Advanced automation, SLAs, multi-queue rules.
  - Ticket templates and dynamic forms.
  - Granular notification rules.
- Your ITSM
  - Queues, escalation, approvals, status workflows.
  - Outbound mail only via explicit actions.
  - Update badge for inbound replies without changing status.
- Gaps
  - Advanced templates/conditional fields.
  - Granular notification rules.
  - Rich form automation.

C. Workflow & Automation Depth
- HaloPSA
  - Event-driven automation (RMM alerts, asset events, contract triggers).
  - Automated routing and closure conditions.
- Your ITSM
  - Basic workflow transitions with limited automation.
  - Manual or queue-based routing.
- Gaps
  - External triggers and automation orchestration.

D. CRM / Client Account Management
- HaloPSA
  - CRM for accounts, contacts, agreements, service history.
  - Designed for MSP multi-client operations.
- Your ITSM
  - Internal user directory only.
  - No CRM or multi-client structure.
- Gaps
  - CRM + client lifecycle management.
  - Multi-tenant client handling.

E. PSA Billing & Contracts
- HaloPSA
  - Contracts, billing, invoicing, profitability tracking.
  - Time entries drive billing.
- Your ITSM
  - No contract or billing layer.
- Gaps
  - PSA finance layer missing.

F. Time Tracking & Projects
- HaloPSA
  - Time tracking, project tasks, resource planning.
- Your ITSM
  - No project module or time entry.
- Gaps
  - Worklog + project workflow missing.

G. Integrations & Ecosystem
- HaloPSA
  - Large integration marketplace (RMM, documentation, finance, monitoring).
- Your ITSM
  - IMAP/SMTP mail only.
- Gaps
  - API connectors and integration ecosystem missing.

H. Assets
- HaloPSA
  - Asset discovery and sync with RMM tools.
  - Lifecycle cost tracking and procurement.
- Your ITSM
  - Basic asset records with category/type structure.
  - Details tab limited to Laptop/Workstation/Desktop/PC.
- Gaps
  - Discovery, sync, costing, and procurement.

I. Reporting & Analytics
- HaloPSA
  - Advanced dashboards, SLA and performance analytics.
- Your ITSM
  - Reports view currently empty by request.
- Gaps
  - Advanced reporting and analytics.

Summary of Major Gaps
1. PSA billing/contracts and finance
2. CRM + multi-client account management
3. Time tracking and project management
4. Integration ecosystem
5. Event-driven automation
6. Advanced asset lifecycle management
7. Reporting and analytics

End of Document
